# Parse pipeline (verified working via our Python decoder):
#   1. Strip last 2 bytes  (CRC = 56 f9), verify with Crc32(body, encryptCode=0xfe7b4873)
#   2. Bytes 0-1 unencrypted = 00 09 (cUdpPacketReliable1)
#   3. XOR-decrypt bytes 2.. with encryptCode 0xfe7b4873 (4-byte chained feedback)
#   4. Strip last byte of decrypted (compression flag, 01 = compressed)
#   5. zlib.decompress to ~250 bytes of plaintext app data
#   6. Decoded plaintext contains: cluster name "swg", address "10.254.0.253",
#      port 44463, branch "swg-main", networkVersion "20100225-17:43"
